# Echothink-Patch: 0017-workspace-context-shell
# Title: Add the Workspace Context side panel shell
# Area: extension
# Depends-On: echothink/0004-bundled-workspace-extension.patch, echothink/0015-side-panel-mode-selector.patch
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The bundled workspace side panel needs a local Workspace Context mode shell so the browser can expose project, domain, wave, approval, artifact, navigation, notification, and action containers before service orchestration exists. Keeping the shell in the MV3 extension avoids native Chromium UI rewrites.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: extension (local sidepanel.html/sidepanel.css/sidepanel.js UI)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.html, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.css, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/sidepanel.js
# Rebase-Risk: low (updates only bundled extension resource files added by echothink/0004)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches, then echothink/0001..0005 and later tail patches including echothink/0014, echothink/0015, and this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178; launch a fresh profile, open the Side Panel, switch to Workspace Context, and verify all required shell sections render without backend availability.
#
# Notes:
# - This patch adds UI containers only. It does not add backend calls, workflow
#   orchestration, approval execution, project/task business logic, privileged
#   bridges, extension permissions, or host permissions.
# - The generic renderer accepts a structured snapshot already available through
#   extension-local storage or internal extension messages and writes textContent
#   only. Links are limited to Echothink-owned HTTPS origins.

